article.headline: Chicago State 86, UTEP 82
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- David Holston scored a game-high 24 points, including two free throws to seal the victory, as Chicago State beat Texas-El Paso 86-82 on Wednesday night. Royce Parran hit a 3-pointer with 8:19 left in the game to give Chicago State (3-3) a 16-point lead, its largest of the game. UTEP chipped away at the deficit and twice pulled to within two points in the final 16 seconds. But Holston made two free throws in the final seconds to preserve the win. UTEP (3-3) led by nine points with 5:24 remaining in the first half, but Chicago State ended the period with an 18-4 run to lead 33-28 at the break. The Cougars had five players score in double figures. Parran scored 20 points and Michael Henderson added 17. Holston and Henderson had nine rebounds apiece, while Cam-Ron Clay had a game-high seven blocks. Stefon Jackson and Marvin Kilgore led the Miners with 21 points each, while Malik Alvin added 17. Jackson and Darren Clarke each had eight rebounds.
